      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Your content should be scene referred and encoded with the ITU-R BT.2100-2 Hybrid Log Gamma (HLG) opto-electrical transfer function (OETF). The system applies the opto-optical transfer function (OOTF) based on peak display brightness and ambient lighting. If you're rendering to a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/quartzcore/cametallayer"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " with a linear colorspace (for floating point EDR layers), you must apply the HLG inverse OETF without normalization, to provide a nominal range of "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "[0, 12]"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "For more information on HLG, see "
            },
            {
              "type": "link",
              "title": "https://www.itu.int/rec/R-REC-BT.2100",
              "destination": "https://www.itu.int/rec/R-REC-BT.2100"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
